U.S. exporters will have theopportunity to sell 170,000 tonnes of wheat to West Africancountries under the Export Enhancement Program, the U.S.Agriculture Department said.    It said in addition to Benin, Cameroon, Ivory Coast, Ghanaand Togo, four more countries -- Burkina Faso, Gabon, Liberiaand Niger -- have been declared eligible under the initiative.    The export sales will be subsidized with commodities fromthe inventory of the Commodity Credit Corporation (CCC), itsaid.    West African countries have already purchased 129,500tonnes of wheat under previously announced export bonusprograms, it noted. Reuter&#3;